To check if ax+by=n  or to check find min(x+y) in this question-:
int i=0;
while(x*i<=z){//value of x or i not changed
    if ((n - i*a)%y == 0){cout<<"Yes"<<endl;return;}
    i++;
}

The above question also clears that Only i++(++i)andi=x(i+=x)changes i value not eg:if(i+1)  

a*b*c = lcm(a*b*c)*gcd(a*b*c)
gcd(a*b) = Largest coprime of a,b  eg:gcd(5,3)=1(coprime of 5,3)
lcm is divisible by gcd

Never use v[-1] , causes runtime error & interviewer will be confused.

Never use set<pair<int,int>> = map cause key cant change in both  hence no use 

Never use set/multiset/map/multimap in competitive prograamming sort the vector instead (large constant because of tree implementation)



